                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/5–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Legation in Syria</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-17T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 17, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. Ur 281 May 13 third para. Connection possibility US representations re
                    Israeli-Arab armistice agreements. Dept has worked closely with Bunche and, as
                    in case <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 209 May 12, has not instructed
                    US reps make representations until so requested by Bunche. Dept appreciates ur
                    suggestion but view fact Bunche has the responsibility for conduct negots
                    desires that question possibility and timing US representations be handled
                    through prior consultation with him as heretofore.</p>
                <pb facs="1037" n="1021" xml:id="pg_1021"/>
                <p>View further revision Bunche proposal Dept concurs representation to Syrian Govt
                    present time not desirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
